place.name: WILBY
place.gazetteerText: WILBY, a parish in Guiltcross district, Norfolk; 1 mile E of Eccles-Road r. station, and 4 SSW of Attleborough. Post town, Attleborough. Acres, 1,400. Real property, £1,769. Pop., 98. Houses, 23. The manor belongs to Sir T. B. Beevor, Bart. The living is a rectory, united with Hargham, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £390.* Patron, J. Goodacre, Esq. The church is old. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
